1. Left-joining questions and tags

# 1.1. Relacione questions y question_tags usando las columnas id y question_id, respectivamente.
questions_with_tags <- left_join(questions, question_tags, by = c("id" = "question_id"))
Warning: Each row in `x` is expected to match at most 1 row in `y`.
# 1.2. Agregue una relacin ms para la tabla tags.
questions_with_tags <- left_join(questions_with_tags, tags, by = c("tag_id" = "id"))

# 1.3. Utilice replace_na para cambiar los NA en la columna tag_name a "only-r".
questions_with_tags <- replace_na(questions_with_tags, list(tag_name = "only-r"))

# 1.4. Por ltimo, almacene el resultado en la variable questions_with_tags.
questions_with_tags

2. Comparing scores across tags

# 2.1. Utilice questions_with_tags y aplique group_by para la variable tag_name.
# 2.2. Aplique summarize para obtener el score promedio de cada pregunta y asgnele el nombre mean_score.
# 2.3. Ordene mean_score en forma descendente.

questions_with_tags %>%
  group_by(tag_name) %>%
  summarize(mean_score = mean(score)) %>%
  arrange(desc(mean_score))

3. Finding gaps between questions and answers

# 3.1. Utilice inner_join para combinar las tablas questions y answers, luego aplique los sufijos "_question" y "_answer", respectivamente.
# 3.2. Agregue una nueva columna utilizando la funcin mutate. La nueva columna se llamar gap y contendr la resta de creation_date_answer y creation_date_question. (creation_date_answer - creation_date_question).

question_answer <- inner_join(questions, answers, by = c("id" = "question_id"), suffix = c("_question", "_answer")) %>%
  mutate(gap = difftime(creation_date_answer, creation_date_question, units = "days"))
Warning: Each row in `x` is expected to match at most 1 row in `y`.
question_answer

4. Joining question and answer counts

# 4.1. Cuente y ordene la columna question_id en la tabla de answers, luego almacene el resultado en la variable answer_counts.
answer_counts <- answers %>%
  count(question_id) %>%
  arrange(desc(n))

answer_counts

# 4.2. Relacione la tabla questions con answer_counts (utilice left_join).
question_answer_counts <- left_join(questions, answer_counts, by = c("id" = "question_id"))

question_answer_counts

# 4.3. Reemplace los valores NA en la columna n con ceros.
question_answer_counts$n[is.na(question_answer_counts$n)] <- 0

# 4.4. Por ltimo almacene el resultado en la variable question_answer_counts
question_answer_counts
